definitions.definition: Of or pertaining to a language family , often grouped into the Afroasiatic language family , spoken in southwestern Ethiopia , some of which use the Ge'ez alphabet, and which are fairly agglutinative , with complex tonal systems.

main_definition: ( linguistics ) Of or pertaining to a language family , often grouped into the Afroasiatic language family , spoken in southwestern Ethiopia , some of which use the Ge'ez alphabet, and which are fairly agglutinative , with complex tonal systems.
